title: Create vespa.json
body:
Implemented Vespa Search
Associated issue #692

To utilize this functionality, follow these steps:

Start Vespa Instance:
Ensure you have a running Vespa instance. If not, refer to Vespa's official documentation for installation instructions.

Add JSON File to Swirl Configuration:
Insert the provided JSON file into your Swirl configuration file.

Restart Swirl:
Restart Swirl to apply the changes.

Now, you can start searching for Vespa content. Use the following command:

swirl search vespa "my query"

title: Gitpod Integration
body:
gitpod.yml file created for gitpod integration

## Description
.gitpod.yml file created for gitpod integration. As we need to run `docker-compose pull && docker-compose up` command to start server before, now using gitpod tasks, we are able to run above command automatically


## Related Issue(s)
Closes #714 

## Screenshots (if appropriate):

Add https://gitpod.io/# at the start of github swirl-search repo url which is https://github.com/swirlai/swirl-search after which I looks something like this https://gitpod.io/#https://github.com/swirlai/swirl-search and hit enter.

You will see something like this:

![image](https://github.com/swirlai/swirl-search/assets/62489114/2dd2f8c4-87dd-4236-ac5a-73e2e419fa62)

After which Dev server will start running automatically as shown below

![image](https://github.com/swirlai/swirl-search/assets/62489114/9ca3f390-b461-4b44-82ea-08f6aeacdc38)

Now create .env file as shown below and paste this line `ALLOWED_HOSTS=localhost,127.0.0.1,*`

![image](https://github.com/swirlai/swirl-search/assets/62489114/a67ad3bb-bde2-4a27-b5e6-f099cdf9a740)


Open docker-compose.yaml file and add below lines
```
    env_file:
      - .env
```
after which it looks something like this

![image](https://github.com/swirlai/swirl-search/assets/62489114/8b99aad7-1c6b-4f08-84ef-d88bd6f9b4ad)

The end result

![image](https://github.com/swirlai/swirl-search/assets/62489114/9ac82570-7e4b-4bf1-9742-b73f84e3d68f)


## Documentation
This line should be added in readme.md so that on clicking this button user will be able to easily create a workspace of swirl instead of changing url
[![Open in Gitpod](https://gitpod.io/button/open-in-gitpod.svg)](https://gitpod.io/#https://github.com/swirlai/swirl-search)

title: Create trello.json
body:
This pull request addresses Issue https://github.com/swirlai/swirl-search/issues/690 and introduces Trello as a new search provider in SwirlAI. With this enhancement, users will now be able to seamlessly integrate Trello boards into their search results, providing a more comprehensive and streamlined search experience.
Changes Made:
Implemented Trello API integration to fetch search results.
Added functionality to parse and display Trello cards within search results.
Enhanced user interface to accommodate Trello-specific information, such as board names and card details.
To run the trello provider add
"searchproviders": { "trello": { "type": "trello.TrelloSearchProvider", "api_key": "YOUR_API_KEY", "api_token": "YOUR_API_TOKEN", } }
to your Swirl Configuration file and restart Swirl and start searching for the Trello content.

title: Update fix_csv.py
body:
I've made the following changes to the code:

Simplified Function Structure:

Removed the main function and replaced it with a single function called fix_csv. Added Exception Handling:

Incorporated a try...except block to handle potential errors that might occur during file operations or CSV processing. Streamlined File Handling:

Utilized the with open(...) as ... statement to automatically handle file opening and closing. This helps improve code readability and ensures that files are closed properly, even if an error occurs. Condensed Argument Parsing:

Integrated the argument parsing directly into the __main__ block, avoiding the need for a separate function for argument parsing. Removed Redundant Checks:

Eliminated redundant checks for file existence and file extension, as these checks were already handled implicitly during file opening. Improved Output Message:

Adjusted the output message to provide more concise and clear information about the operation. This condensed version maintains the original functionality while reducing unnecessary code complexity. It should be easier to read and maintain.

title: Add support for Ollama, Palm, Claude-2, Cohere, Replicate Llama2, CodeLlama, Hugging Face (100+LLMs) - using LiteLLM
body:
This PR adds support for the above mentioned LLMs using LiteLLM https://github.com/BerriAI/litellm/ 
LiteLLM is a lightweight package to simplify LLM API calls - use any llm as a drop in replacement for gpt-3.5-turbo. 

Example
```python
from litellm import completion

## set ENV variables
os.environ["OPENAI_API_KEY"] = "openai key"
os.environ["COHERE_API_KEY"] = "cohere key"

messages = [{ "content": "Hello, how are you?","role": "user"}]

# openai call
response = completion(model="gpt-3.5-turbo", messages=messages)

# cohere call
response = completion(model="command-nightly", messages)

# anthropic call
response = completion(model="claude-instant-1", messages=messages)
```
